<p>Converting <strong>ounce to mls (ml)</strong> is primarily used for:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Cooking and mixology: Adapting recipes that use volume measurements fro=
m the U.S. customary system (fluid ounces, cups) to the metric system (mill=
iliters, liters), which is the international standard.</li>
<li>Labeling and commerce: Meeting labeling requirements in metric-system c=
ountries for food and pharmaceutical products originating from the U.S.</li=
>
<li>Science and medicine: The <strong>oz to ml conversion</strong> is essen=
tial for accurately translating liquid volumes for calculations, dosages, a=
nd medical procedures.</li>
<li>Engineering: Simplifying unit conversions between different measurement=
 systems in technical calculations.</li>
</ul>
<p>=F0=9F=9F=A7 If you have any other questions about the <strong>ounces to=
